mmer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9963751214600606, \"rank\": 0.0015124158253300346, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport|Olympics\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 257}, {\"ngram\": \"a single gold medal\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 323}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 342}, {\"ngram\": \"the mood\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games had brought a number of major breakthroughs, most notably first global medals forKeely HodgkinsonandJosh Kerr, and the first real sense of a team ready to move on from the Super Saturday generation of 2012.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"major breakthroughs\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"most notably first global medals\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"HodgkinsonandJosh Kerr\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"the first real sense\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"the Super Saturday generation\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eyes then, were already on Paris, where over the next 10 days there is realistic hope Britain could enjoy their bestOlympicson the track since London.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 662, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998603926, \"rank\": 1.3971821370360082e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin